reviewText: Plagued by clichés, stereotypes, and sexual innuendo, this poorly-constructed film is rife with cringe-worthy moments. What might have been a fun and light-hearted story instead kept me wondering when the insanity would end. - This is an obvious ripoff of My Best Friend's Wedding - a much better film, though it has its own flaws, to be sure.
summary: Flimsy plot with a lousy execution.

Title: The Wedding Pact

reviewText: I was totally mislead with all these 'great' reviews... how is that possible when IMDB has like 200 votes with a 1-Star rating!!For starters-- there is tons of sexual stuff, drug use, etc. Umm not what I was expecting from this 'family fun' flick.The love story is non existent-- the movie focuses on the main guy and his road trip to see Haylie Duff's character.Haylie and the lead guy share like 15 minutes total screen time.I was thinking that this would be a cute chick flick/Hallmark style movie-- forget it! And definitely not family friendly, unless your kids like fighting, drug use, a girl in lingerie stripper dancing, another girl straddling the main guy, a couple doing it in the back of the main guys car, and the fiancee snorting coke and downing shots-- wholesome family fun!!! Not!I was really hoping to love this movie and I'm very easy to please in the whole chick flick department, but this movie is more a guys roadtrip movie, with a relationship forming at the end.What a waste :(
summary: Not Even Worth 1 Star--- Are all the other reviews fake??
Title: The Wedding Pact
